n: 0 0 20px 0;">ALCOA dominated the industry so handily that in 1938, FDR&#=
8217;s Justice Department sued it for antitrust based not on rapacious prac=
tices, but on market share alone.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Hall invented =
a technology (and protected it with patents) to manufacture a product with =
structurally superior unit economics in order to bring down costs and both =
successfully compete in existing markets and create new ones.&#160;</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Or take </span><strong>Carnegie Steel</strong><span>.</=
span><strong> </strong><span>In 1860, when Andrew Carnegie was dabbling in =
iron investments, the superior steel was so expensive to make that it was o=
nly made in small batches; the US </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/re=
