But in 1872, Carnegie saw the Bessemer Process in action at a plant in Engl=
and, and introduced it to his J. Edgar Thompson Steelworks in 1875. By the =
turn of the century, the US produced over 11 million tons of steel, and Car=
negie was its largest and most profitable producer.</span></p><div class=3D=
